    <body>
      <trans-unit id="8473" identifier="36710e8e1305fd9b7986bb20340cf7af">
        <source>Make variables called:</source>
        <target>crwdns8473:0crwdne8473:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8474" identifier="ca2ef64e6b857d4a4bbb8e7613c74f04">
        <source>“decimal number” and set its value to the input number given by the
end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns8474:0crwdne8474:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li/ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8475" identifier="c6695ad2fbafce6c699ceb291df121c9">
        <source>“bit value” and set its value to ‘1’.</source>
        <target>crwdns8475:0crwdne8475:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8476" identifier="f5491124f5a0664b3147bef42d7ad83b">
        <source>Find the smallest bit value which is larger than the “decimal number”
by doubling value of “bit value” until it is bigger than the “decimal
number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8476:0crwdne8476:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/ul/li[2]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8477" identifier="e4b61b852c7a802c4f3d77e10503a52f">
        <source>Set the variable “bit value” to 1 and find the smallest “bit value” which
is larger than “decimal number” by multiplying “bit value” by 2
(Use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:() * ()&lt;/code&gt; block under “Operators” to multiply the “bit
value” by 2) until it is larger than “decimal number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8477:0crwdne8477:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8478" identifier="8c7a6ce24b080a1cf2de51961db232fc">
        <source>You can do this by using a &lt;code&gt;scratch:repeat until &amp;lt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; loop.</source>
        <target>crwdns8478:0crwdne8478:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8479" identifier="1cc0fd44cb465656f458b0471378dba5">
        <source>Now divide the “bit value” by 2 and check if “decimal number” is greater
than or equal to “bit value”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8479:0crwdne8479:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8480" identifier="a8e42e2a4d731e73f5c7a71b3e52d4f2">
        <source>If it is, play a high note and subtract “bit value” from the “decimal number”.</source>
        <target>crwdns8480:0crwdne8480:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8481" identifier="7fba89437f54b579d03950f6d2bbe3dd">
        <source>If not, play a low note.</source>
        <target>crwdns8481:0crwdne8481:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8482" identifier="0a304bde332c26a02cd7007b488d913a">
        <source>Repeat until “bit value” is equal to 1.</source>
        <target>crwdns8482:0crwdne8482:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8483" identifier="651dac9b39b0f62c5c4827427c363f0f">
        <source>To play a musical note use the block
&lt;code&gt;scratch:play note (60 v) for (0.5) beats&lt;/code&gt; beats under the “Sound”.
Type in the number “72” for a high note and “48” for a low note.</source>
        <target>crwdns8483:0crwdne8483:0</target>
        <note>Context: List Item&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]</note>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
